    {
      "id": "/page/0/TextInlineMath/11",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">A famous subclass of <math display=\"inline\">S</math> is the class of distribution functions with regularly varying tails; see [3]. For a positive measurable function <math display=\"inline\">f</math>, we write <math display=\"inline\">f \\in \\mathcal{R}(\\alpha)</math>for <math display=\"inline\">\\alpha \\in \\mathbb{R}</math> (f is regularly varying with index <math display=\"inline\">\\alpha</math>) if</p>",
