      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">In addition, the lognormal, the two Benktander families, and the heavy-tailed Weibull (shape parameter less than 1) belong to <math display=\"inline\">S</math>; see again Table 1.2.6 in [4]. However, a direct proof of this is more difficult than that for the regularly varying case. Subexponentiality is typically established via an integral test for the hazard rate known as <i>Pitman's criterion</i> [2].</p>",
